commText: Mohit Sharma to Zampa, B0$ Zampa Run Out!! 1 run completed. Gee, we have seen everything tonight. Just when you thought it couldn't get any worse for RR, it just did. B1$ Zampa lofted this off the toe end and teased the fielder (Shankar) running back from cover. Abhinav came sprinting in from sweeper to his right and collected the ball cleanly before sending a rifle-like throw at the batting end. The call was always for two and Zampa was casually trundling to the batting end probably assuming the only he was could get out was a direct hit. And bam! The ball bounced off the outfield and kept low before striking the stumps dead. B2$

formatValue: RR post their lowest total in Jaipur.

commText: Shami to Boult, B0$ Bowled!! The off pole goes for a walk. I0$ wobble seam full delivery (almost a yorker) aiming for the base of the stumps. Boult gave himself a bit too much room and failed to get bat on the ball, by the time he tried to bring his bat down - the stumps were in a mess. B1$

Noor Ahmad to Boult, B0$, whew! Where did that come from? A gentle toss up on leg-stump, Boult strides across and swipes it over mid-wicket for a mighty maximum. Tewatia is having a word with Boult, nothing sledgy though...
Rashid Khan to Zampa, 1 run, floated up outside off, driven out to long-off

Rashid Khan to Boult, 1 run, B0$ Not too sure if he got hand on it. Floaty legbreak outside off, Boult chips the drive straight back and beats the outstretched right hand of Rashid, it went rapidly and the leaping effort from the bowler only helped him get some fingertips perhaps

Rashid Khan to Hetmyer, B0$ Lbw!! Hetmyer has no option but to walk. No more reviews for RR. That's plumb. Drifts in on a good length and skids straight with a hint of inward turn. Hetmyer with a big stride forward doesn't get bat on ball. Misses the inside edge by a long way and was struck dead in front of middle pole. He almost started to walk even before the umpire's verdict and quickly realised that there weren't any reviews left as well. B1$
Noor Ahmad to Boult, B0$, outside edge and four! Boult slashes at a short and wide of off and the edge flies away past the keeper to his right

Noor Ahmad to Dhruv Jurel, B0$ Lbw!! The Afghan spinners are on a roll. The fullish googly from Noor Ahmad. Got the ball to land in line with leg stump and spun towards middle and off. Dhruv Jurel got beaten on the inside edge on the attempted flick and was caught dead in front. The review was more in hope and it looked pretty straight to the naked eye. Ball tracker proves it was gonna hit the top of middle and off. B1$

formatValue: Dhruv Jurel lbw b Noor Ahmad 9(8) [4s-1]

commText: Joshua Little to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, dropped. Tewatia the culprit. Short of a length delivery angling across, Dhruv pokes and gets a thick edge. First slip moved to the right but spilled it

Noor Ahmad to Dhruv Jurel, B0$, oh what bravery to play a reverse sweep to a tough wristy first ball when the team is six down for almost nothing. Dhruv manages to place it wide of short third man and it runs away for four

Noor Ahmad to Padikkal, B0$ Bowled!! The Afghan wristies are spinning a web around RR. Padikkal plays an I don't know if that's spinning back or going away kind of defence. Stood way too leg-side of the ball. This wasn't the googly as he expected. Turned away to beat the bat and smash the off stump out of the ground. RR are reeling. Now Hardik can attack with more close in fielders to the lower-order. B1$

Rashid Khan to Riyan Parag, B0$ Lbw!! This was coming. Rashid not the easiest to read off the hand even if you are a modern day great. So he will fancy his chances v Riyan, which is why he wouldn't have been too unhappy about bowling a short ball for two than a single the previous ball. Googly from Rashid Khan, pitching just outside off stump, Riyan couldn't read it, played across the line, just sneaked past the inside edge to hit him in line with off stump. Ball-tracker shows ball smashing middle of middle stump, so the review too is gone for RR. The impact sub doesn't work. Unfortunately, Riyan was up against a giant. Brilliant captaincy from Hardik to not hold back Rashid for later and go for the kill. B1$

formatValue: Riyan Parag lbw b Rashid Khan 4(6)

commText: Rashid Khan to Ashwin, B0$ Bowled!! Ashwin had absolutely no clue how to play Rashid Khan in that over. First missed a short ball, then missed a drive on the fuller length. Now Rashid Khan bowls on the stumps knowing Ashwin is not reading his leggies. The batter stays in the crease and tries to push it through the off-side, past the outside edge and rattling the off stump. Wonder if Ashwin was searching for that googly but Rashid never bowled that ball. B1$

Joshua Little to Samson, B0$ Caught by Hardik Pandya!! Oh Sanju! Not again. Surely not after looking so promising. The heartbreak for a cricket fan to see him not convert a start. This was a simple length delivery just around off stump. Sanju moved across the stumps to flick to mid-wicket. Wonder why he did that because the left-armer's angle across RHB is anyway going to make it tougher. This ball did seem to seam away a wee bit. Massive leading edge. Hardik waits ages under the ball at cover and takes a very good catch. Sanju stares at the pitch. Still staring and looking back as he drags himself off unwillingly. Big, big wicket. Sanju was looking so good and the over where Little was losing the battle, he gets the main man. B1$

formatValue: Samson c Hardik Pandya b Joshua Little 30(20) [4s-3 6s-1]

commText: Joshua Little to Padikkal, B0$, oh what a shot! Padikkal has played some gorgeous shots this season. Length delivery outside off stump, Padikkal waits and gives the full face of the bat to the ball with a punch and it races wide of mid-off
Joshua Little to Samson, B0$, Sanju doesn't want to let Joshua Little settle. Sets base for a solid on the rise smash wide of mid-off. Joshua Little starts with a length ball and gets punished
Rashid Khan to Samson, 1 run, tight around middle, Samson knocks it to mid-on

Rashid Khan to Samson, B0$ Jaiswal Run Out!! Cut away nicely. Excellent diving save by Abhinav! Oh yes-no, both Sanju and Jaiswal at the keeper's end and Sanju gets back to his crease. Disaster for RR. This was a shortish ball, Sanju timed that nicely, Jaiswal thought he had a run there with this being a half stop and the fielder had to fetch the ball before throwing. Sanju was out of the crease, but saw the fielding and went back. Jaiswal was already at his end by then and the fielder had ample time to relay a calm throw to Rashid's end. Problem for Jaiswal was the half stop went straight to the man at short third man. B1$
Shami to Samson, B0$, oh shot! Third man in, waited for this short of length delivery to arrive and just opened the bat face last second to guide it between backward point and short third man

Hardik Pandya to Samson, B0$, now, now, that's middled and muscled. Hardik Pandya tried the slower ball, but it sat up on this pitch, Samson stays back and plays a get out of my sight pull over mid-wicket for a 95m hit
Hardik Pandya to Samson, B0$, Sanju hints at shuffling, Hardik Pandya drops it short expecting the batter to back away but Sanju gets back to his original stance and pulls this over mid-wicket

Shami to Jaiswal, B0$, they have a deep backward square leg but mid-wicket so open. Now that is interesting. But Shami would have wanted to finish close to off stump if the idea was to make Jaiswal play across the line against the length ball moving away. This was too straight and dismissed with a flick shot

Shami to Jaiswal, B0$, yikes! The airtime that ball had was a sight to behold. Shami bowls leg-side and pays the price. Length delivery, oh yes I could have a pick up shot reckons Jaiswal and times it brilliantly well. Sails and hits the roof over the long leg ropes

Hardik Pandya to Buttler, B0$ Caught by Mohit Sharma!! Edgeddd and straight to short third man. How perfectly could you place a fielder there? Looks like Hardik pushed a fielder back to the leg-side ropes and called third man in. Simple Test match ball - back of a length outside off stump, the ball seams away, Buttler thought he could have a backfoot drive but this one did bounce nicely and the thick edge flew straight to Mohit, who was very alert. B1$

formatValue: Buttler c Mohit Sharma b Hardik Pandya 8(6) [4s-2]

commText: Hardik Pandya to Buttler, B0$, down leg again, Buttler flicks through backward square leg, no one there and it's back to back fours. He is rolling now

Hardik Pandya to Buttler, B0$, the Jos Buttler defence flick. Literally just a defence and it speeds off the bat. Is this the shot that gets him back into the rhythm? Hardik Pandya tried the outswinger, but bowled leg-side, Buttler stood solid and just met the ball with a great base. Balance, timing, placement everything spot on as it went to the right of mid-on
